'''Benjamin "Ben" Polak''' (born 22 December 1961) is a British professor of [[economics]] and management and [[Provost (education)|Provost]] at [[Yale University]].<ref>[http://cowles.econ.yale.edu/faculty/vita/cv_polak.pdf CV] for Benjamin Polak at Yale</ref> From 1999-2001 Polak was the Henry Kohn Associate Professor of Economics<ref>[http://cowles.econ.yale.edu/news/polak/bp_99-07-19_kohn.htm Polak Assumes Kohn Associate Chair in Economics] Yale Bulletin & Calendar, June 21-July 19, 1999</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Yale School of Management - Faculty - Benjamin Polak|url=http://mba.yale.edu/faculty/profiles/polak.shtml|accessdate=1 April 2012}}</ref> and is now the inaugural [[William C. Brainard]] Professor of Economics.<ref>[http://opa.yale.edu/news/article.aspx?id=6209 Benjamin Polak Is the Inaugural William C. Brainard Professor] from Yale University Office of Public Affairs, November 14, 2008</ref> In January 2013, he became the Provost of Yale University.<ref>https://messages.yale.edu/messages/University/univmsgs/detail/87273</ref>

Polak specialises in microeconomic theory and has published 19 peer reviewed papers in leading journals, and is Associate editor of the [[Journal of Economic Theory]].

==ECON 159: Game Theory==

In fall 2007, Polak participated in the [[Open Yale Courses]] initiative, recording the 24 lecture series and making all course materials freely available on the Internet.<ref>[http://oyc.yale.edu/economics/game-theory/ ECON159 Game Theory] with Professor Benjamin Polak at Open Yale Courses</ref> Polak describes the motivation for his participation in the scheme as delivering an [[Ivy League]] standard education to a wider audience, "It<U+2019>s not the full Yale experience, unfortunately, but it<U+2019>s something.<U+201D><ref>[http://web.archive.org/web/20071111202243/http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/22335 Now on Web, Yale classroom open to public] by Ruth Kim in Yale Daily News on Friday November 9, 2007</ref>

